 "cells": [

   "source": [
    "def modplot(e):\n",
    "    #function to plot modulus of complex vector\n",
    "    e = np.asarray(e.T)\n",
    "    plt.plot(modulus(e))\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "def frameplot(X,movshape):\n",
    "    #plot a single frame\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots()\n",
    "    axes.imshow(X.reshape(movshape), cmap='Greys')\n",
    "    axes.set_title('snapshot frame = 1')\n",
    "    \n",
    "def modulus(X):\n",
    "    #function to calculate modulus of complex vector\n",
    "    modX = np.sqrt(X.real**2 + X.imag**2)\n",
    "    return modX"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import cv2\n",
    "from numpy.linalg import svd, inv, eig, pinv"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1 - Load Video"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def read_video_gray(name, n_frames):\n",
    "    cap = cv2.VideoCapture('./{}'.format(name))\n",
    "    bw_frames = []\n",
    "    i = 0\n",
    "    while cap.isOpened() and i < n_frames:\n",
    "        ret, frame = cap.read()\n",
    "        arr = np.array(frame)\n",
    "        # https://www.dynamsoft.com/blog/insights/image-processing/image-processing-101-color-space-conversion/\n",
    "        # using the weighted method (luminosity method)\n",
    "        im = (0.299*arr[:,:,0] + 0.587*arr[:,:,1] + 0.114*arr[:,:,2])/255\n",
    "        im = 1-im\n",
    "        bw_frames.append(im)\n",
    "        i += 1\n",
    "    return np.array(bw_frames)\n",
    "\n",
    "def read_video_color(name, n_frames):\n",
    "    cap = cv2.VideoCapture('./{}'.format(name))\n",
    "    frames = []; bw_frames = []\n",
    "    i = 0\n",
    "    while cap.isOpened() and i < n_frames:\n",
    "        ret, frame = cap.read()\n",
    "        arr = np.array(frame)\n",
    "        frames.append(arr)\n",
    "    return np.array(frames)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#60Hz video, \n",
    "#taking 360 frames, 6 seconds of video\n",
    "f = 3*60\n",
    "#choose between movies\n",
    "titles = ['Race','Ski']\n",
    "mov = read_video_gray(name='monte_carlo.mov',n_frames=f); name = 0 #to indicate figure names\n",
    "#mov = read_video_gray(name='ski_drop.mov',n_frames=f); name = 1 #to indicate figure names\n",
    "\n",
    "#get res, number of pixels for monte_carlo.mov\n",
    "p = mov[0].shape[0] * mov[0].shape[1]\n",
    "movshape = mov[0].shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "resolution = (1112, 1872) , frames =  180\n",
      "pixel =  2081664\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print('resolution =', movshape, ', frames = ', len(mov))\n",
    "print('pixel = ',p)\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, sharey=True)\n",
    "axes[0].imshow(mov[0], cmap='Greys')\n",
    "axes[1].imshow(mov[100], cmap='Greys')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('{} snapshot frame = 1'.format(titles[name]))\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('{} snapshot frame = 99'.format(titles[name]))\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('./figures/{}_snapshots.png'.format(titles[name]), bbox_inches = 'tight', dpi =200)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 2 - Format data for DMD"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "D (2081664, 180)\n",
      "X (2081664, 179) Y (2081664, 179)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "D = np.empty(shape=(p,f))\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(0,f):\n",
    "    D[:,i] = mov[i].reshape(-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X has frames {1,...,119}, Y has frames {2,...,120}\n",
    "X = D[:,0:(f-1)]; Y = D[:,1:f]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('D', D.shape)\n",
    "print('X', X.shape, 'Y', Y.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "del mov;"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3 - Dynamic Mode Decomposition\n",
    "\n",
    "$Y = A X \\rightarrow A=YX^{\\dagger} $  with $X^{\\dagger} = (U\\Sigma V^*)^{-1}$\n",
    "\n",
    "Exact DMD [73], $\\tilde{A} \\in (f,f)$ instead of $A \\in (p,p)$\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\tilde{A} = U^* Y V \\Sigma^{-1}$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1) Exact DMD method, with reduced $\\tilde{A}$ matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "U shape = (2081664, 179), S shape = (179, 179), V shape = (179, 179)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "U,S,Vh = svd(X.astype('float64'), full_matrices=False,compute_uv=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('U shape = {}, S shape = {}, V shape = {}'.format(U.shape, np.diag(S).shape, Vh.shape))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "A shapes = (179, 179)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "B = Y @ Vh.T @ pinv(np.diag(S))\n",
    "At = np.matmul(U.T,B)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('A shapes =', At.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2) Eigen Decomposition"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "eigval size =  179 , eigvec shape = (179, 179)\n",
      "zero real [] zero imag [0, 47, 178]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "eigval, eigvec = eig(At); \n",
    "\n",
    "print('eigval size = ',eigval.size,', eigvec shape =',eigvec.shape )\n",
    "\n",
    "zero_real = []; zero_imag = []\n",
    "for i in range(0,f-1):\n",
    "    if eigval[i].real == 0.:\n",
    "        zero_real.append(i)\n",
    "    elif eigval[i].imag == 0.:\n",
    "        zero_imag.append(i)\n",
    "print('zero real', zero_real,'zero imag', zero_imag)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot the complex numbers\n",
    "x = eigval.real; y = eigval.imag\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "c = plt.Circle( (0, 0), 1 , fill = False, linestyle='--',alpha=0.75 )\n",
    "ax.set_aspect(1)\n",
    "ax.add_artist(c)\n",
    "ax.scatter(x, y, s=3, c='red')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Imaginary')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Real')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlim([-1.2,1.2])\n",
    "ax.set_ylim([-1.2,1.2])\n",
    "ax.set_title('{} eigenvalues'.format(titles[name]))\n",
    "plt.savefig('./figures/{}_eigenvalues.png'.format(titles[name]), bbox_inches = 'tight', dpi =200)\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3) DMD modes and eigenvalue scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "DMD modes: $\\varphi = U w \\in (p,f)$, where $w$ = eigvec of matrix $\\tilde{A}$\n",
    "\n",
    "X reconstruction $X_{\\text{DMD}} = \\Phi \\Omega^n b$, $n \\in \\{1,2,3...,N\\}$\n",
    "\n",
    "with amplitudes $b = (\\Phi^* \\Phi)^{-1}\\Phi^* X_0$ and $\\Omega = Diag(\\exp(\\omega_m))$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "phi shape = (2081664, 179), b shape = (179, 1)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "phi = np.matmul(U,eigvec)\n",
    "#phi = np.matmul(B,eigvec) @ pinv(np.diag(eigval))\n",
    "\n",
    "phih = np.asmatrix(phi).H\n",
    "\n",
    "g1 = pinv(np.matmul(phih,phi))\n",
    "g2 = np.matmul(phih, X[:,0])\n",
    "b = np.matmul(g1,g2.T)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('phi shape = {}, b shape = {}'.format(phi.shape, b.shape))\n",
    "del phih; del g1; del g2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x24686294b80>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(modulus(np.asarray(b)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4) Filtering out small frequencies\n",
    "\n",
    "background with $||\\omega_m|| \\approx 0$ or $||\\mu_m|| \\approx 1$ \n",
    "\n",
    "foreground with $||\\omega_m|| >>> 0$ or $||\\mu_m|| - 1 >>> 0$ "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mu_mod = np.sqrt(eigval.real**2+eigval.imag**2)\n",
    "l = np.argmin(np.abs(mu_mod - 1))\n",
    "l"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot modulus of eigen values\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.plot(mu_mod, c='red')\n",
    "ax.stem(l, mu_mod[l],markerfmt=' ',linefmt ='--', basefmt= ' ')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('modulus')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('eigenvalue #')\n",
    "ax.set_title('{} eigenvalues modulus'.format(titles[name]))\n",
    "plt.savefig('./figures/{}_modulus_eval.png'.format(titles[name]), bbox_inches = 'tight', dpi =200)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5) Construct Lowrank\n",
    "\n",
    "$X = X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Low-Rank}} + X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Sparse}}$\n",
    "\n",
    "$X_t = b_p \\varphi_p \\exp(\\omega_p t)$ where $p \\in $ null_omega"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "phi[l] shape = (1, 2081664), eigval[l] shape = (1, 1), b[l] shape = (1, 1)\n",
      "eigval[l] = [[1.0000546+0.j]], b[l] = [[777.00048873+2.77354754e-11j]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Filter background\n",
    "# phi = (p,f)\n",
    "# eigvalmat = (f,f)\n",
    "# b = (f,1)\n",
    "phi_lr= np.matrix(phi[:,l], dtype = 'complex64');\n",
    "b_lr = b[l]\n",
    "eigval_lr = np.matrix(eigval[l].astype('complex64'))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('phi[l] shape = {}, eigval[l] shape = {}, b[l] shape = {}'.format(phi_lr.shape, eigval_lr.shape, b_lr.shape))\n",
    "print('eigval[l] = {}, b[l] = {}'.format(eigval_lr, b_lr))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_lowrank = np.empty((p,f), dtype ='complex64')\n",
    "for t in range(0,f):\n",
    "    Xl = eigval_lr**t * b_lr * phi_lr\n",
    "    X_lowrank[:,t] = Xl\n",
    "\n",
    "X_lowrank_modulus = modulus(X_lowrank)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "frameplot(X_lowrank_modulus[:,105], movshape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6) Sparse matrix construction\n",
    "\n",
    "$X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Sparse}} = X - |X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Lowrank}}| $\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#sparse matrix\n",
    "X_sparse = D-X_lowrank_modulus; del X_lowrank_modulus;"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7) Residual Correction\n",
    "$X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Sparse}} \\leftarrow  X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Sparse}} + R$\n",
    "\n",
    "$X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Lowrank}} \\leftarrow X_{\\text{DMD}}^{\\text{Lowrank}} - R$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#residual matrix\n",
    "R = X_sparse.copy()\n",
    "R[R>0] = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "#Xf_lowrank = X_lowrank + R\n",
    "\n",
    "#final video without background\n",
    "X_sparse_mod = modulus(X_sparse - R)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "del R; del X_sparse;"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, sharey=True)\n",
    "axes[0].imshow(1-X_sparse_mod[:,0].reshape(movshape), cmap='Greys')\n",
    "axes[1].imshow(1-X_sparse_mod[:,99].reshape(movshape), cmap='Greys')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('{} snapshot frame = 1'.format(titles[name]))\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('{} snapshot frame = 99'.format(titles[name]))\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('./figures/{}_foreground.png'.format(titles[name]), bbox_inches = 'tight', dpi =200)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 5 - Save video"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "duration = 3\n",
    "fps = 60\n",
    "out = cv2.VideoWriter('{}_foreground.mp4'.format(titles[name]), cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'mp4v'), \n",
    "                      fps, (movshape[1], movshape[0]), False)\n",
    "for t in range(fps * duration):\n",
    "    invbw = X_sparse_mod[:,t].reshape(movshape)\n",
    "    frame = 255*invbw\n",
    "    data = frame.astype('uint8')\n",
    "    out.write(data)\n",
    "out.release()"
   ]
  },
